choices.text:
trying to figure out how the fuck I can get over to Pakistan. I don’t hate the place really, I just know that nobody cares who I am there, and I’ll have much more access to girls there but with none of the culture or party scene of the West. I’d like to find some girls where authentic Pakistani culture is nourished, rather than simply where it’s coerced.
 
I was also thinking, if all else fails, I could apple white wedding and change my name to Ali Qureshi or something. I look Muslim (long, dark hair, tanned skin) and I can sure learn to talk like a desi fucker, right?
 
God help me
 
Some advice then please my fellow citizens of Oslo.
 
--------------------- 
 
2 Months later, the synopsis of our correspondence boils down to this:


---------------------

His misconceptions, How He Is, Suggestions:

- He is 'very afraid', constantly retrains himself from telling people why he can't see them or whatever, when really he should be putting his foot down and telling them why he wants some time alone before finals.

- He is worried that his current life choices (school, study, 40 hrs weeks) are keep him from the life he wants.  But he doesn't want to snap his entire life up and fly to Pakistan, after all the years he's been arguing with his parents.

- His grades are good, but he prefers to surf in person, or watch FB surf
